\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 A Calliope document consists of a sequence of musical systems.  The Calliope window shows your document formatted as it would be on the printed page.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Each page of a Calliope document allows for margins at the top, bottom, left and right edges of the page.    Top and bottom running titles appear in the top and bottom margin areas.  Left and right binding margins may also be specified in addition to the .  All margins may be given different values for even-numbered and odd-numbered pages..  In addition, systems may be indented on the right and left on an individual basis.  The rulers, described later, may be shown in addition to the other regions.  Every part of the page (including the margins) can be viewed in the document window.  The various regions are illustrated here, where margin widths are exaggerated to show them:\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qc\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 {{\NeXTGraphic4 graphic_8.eps \width4420\height5120
}¬} \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 All the typing and editing you do occurs in the body region (and occasionally in the margins, where certain editorial marks may be placed). Musical systems are automatically placed in the body region according to standard layout conventions, although you may exert some control over the layout of systems for unusual circumstances.  Systems flow through your document from the body of one page to the body of the next.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\keepn\fi0\sb360\sa200\li0\ri0\f1\fs48\b1\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The Window\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\ql\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Calliope displays one page of the document in a window.  Depending on the size of your display screen, the entire page can be displayed, or the window can be display part of a page.   Buttons and a text field provide the means for viewing any page of the document.  The scrollbars may be used to scroll to different parts of the page if the window has been made too small to show the whole page, as shown here:\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qc\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0  {{\NeXTGraphic4 graphic_7.eps \width7100\height8320
}¬} \par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 The first thing to notice is that Calliope displays the musicwork on a light gray background, not the usual white background.  The reason for this is to improve legibility and to reduce eyestrain.  Of course, the background of the printed version of the page will be the normal color of the paper.  Text and graphics are shown in black, indicating that they will appear on the printed page.  Any non-printing information appears in dark grey, and any selected information appears in white.  These are illustrated later.  It is possible to change the colours that make up various parts of the display using the Preferences.  \par
